We address the 101companies scenarios with XQuery.
See the Makefile for running some tests.
We use the BaseX implementation available for Java platform from:
	http://www.inf.uni-konstanz.de/dbis/basex/index
Requires Java 6.

Tested with this version of BaseX:

$ java -cp ../library/basex/BaseX61.jar org.basex.BaseX -h
BaseX 6.1; DBIS, University of Konstanz
Usage: BaseX [-dioqsvVxz] [query] [-c]
  [query]    query file
  -c<cmd>    database commands
  -d         debug mode
  -i<file>   XML input
  -o<file>   output file
  -q<expr>   query expression
  -s<pars>   serialization parameters
  -v/V       show (all) process info
  -w         wrap query result to xml
  -z         skip query output

The version without the update facility (has a different cut implementation)
uses Saxon from:
	http://saxon.sourceforge.net/ or http://www.saxonica.com/

Tested with this version of Saxon:

$ java -jar ../library/saxon/saxon9he.jar
No source file name
Saxon-HE 9.2.1.2J from Saxonica
Usage: see http://www.saxonica.com/documentation/using-xsl/commandline.html
Options: 
   ...